{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The equation for the cost of a 3D-IC is:𝐶 3𝐷 = ∑ 𝑛 𝑖=1 𝐶 𝑖 𝑌 stacking 𝑛-1 𝑌 𝑇𝑆𝑉 (9)where 𝑛 is the number of stacked dies [51].",
    "We utilize a normalized cost metric to compare the cost of each die.",
    "Since the three systems considered with the above- 91.9 8.1 ReRAM Systolic Array 32.8 mentioned NoC configurations utilize the same number of stacks, the normalized cost of die (𝑑𝑖𝑒_𝐴) with respect to (𝑑𝑖𝑒_𝐵) can be defined as:𝐶 𝑛𝑜𝑟𝑚 (𝑑𝑖𝑒_𝐴|𝑑𝑖𝑒_𝐵) = 𝑌 𝑑𝑖𝑒-𝐵 × 𝑁 𝑑𝑖𝑒-𝐵 𝑌 𝑑𝑖𝑒-𝐴 × 𝑁 𝑑𝑖𝑒-𝐴(10)The normalized cost for our analysis becomes a function of 𝐷 0, 𝛼, 𝜙 𝑤𝑎𝑓𝑒𝑟, and 𝐴 𝑑𝑖𝑒.",
    "Here, 𝐷 0, 𝛼, and 𝜙 𝑤𝑎𝑓𝑒𝑟 are physical parameters.",
    "The only controllable parameter influencing the cost is the area of each die."
  ],
